
[1]usage

   U'SAGE, n s as z. [See Use.]

   1. Treatment; an action or series of actions performed by one person
   towards another, or which directly affect him; as good usage; ill
   usage; hard usage. Gentle usage will often effect what harsh usage will
   not. The elephant may be governed by mild usage.

   2. Use, or long continued use; custom; practice. Uninterrupted usage
   for a long time, or immemorial usage constitutes prescription. Custom
   is a local usage; prescription is a personal usage. In language, usage
   is the foundation of all rules.

   Of things once received and confirmed by use, long usage is a law
   sufficient.

   3. Manners; behavior. Obs.
